Description: CVE-2025-14017 - Fix LDAP thread-safety by calling ldap_init() before setting options
 When doing multi-threaded LDAPS transfers (LDAP over TLS) with libcurl,
 changing TLS options in one thread would inadvertently change them globally
 and therefore possibly also affect other concurrently setup transfers.
 Disabling certificate verification for a specific transfer could
 unintentionally disable the feature for other threads as well.
 .
 The fix moves the ldap_init()/ldap_sslinit() call before the
 ldap_set_option() calls, and passes the server handle instead of NULL
 to ldap_set_option(), ensuring options are set per-connection rather
 than globally.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/39d1976b7f709a516e3243338ebc0443bdd8d56d
Author: Daniel Stenberg <daniel@haxx.se>
Last-Update: 2025-06-04
