Description: CVE-2026-12064 - config2setopts: use default protocol properly
 The curl command-line tool skipped SSH host key verification setup when
 invoked with a schemeless URL together with --proto-default sftp (or scp).
 The tool layer inferred the scheme independently of libcurl, so libcurl
 honoured CURLOPT_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL and connected over SFTP/SCP while the
 tool never installed CURLOPT_SSH_HOST_PUBLIC_KEY_SHA256 or
 CURLOPT_SSH_KNOWNHOSTS, allowing a silent connection to an unverified
 SSH host. This patch reworks url_proto_and_rewrite() in
 src/config2setopts.c so that when --proto-default is set the tool uses
 CURLU_NO_GUESS_SCHEME and applies the configured default protocol via
 proto_token(), keeping the tool's protocol view in sync with libcurl.
 Also refreshes the --proto-default documentation and adds tests 1724,
 1725 and 2036.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/ab3bb8cd8be8f9d4acb97da0418abc279182041e
Author: Daniel Stenberg <daniel@haxx.se>
Bug: https://curl.se/docs/CVE-2026-12064.html
Last-Update: 2026-07-08
